Federal Register: 109. Dodine (dodecylguanidine monoacetate) (CAS No. 002439-10-3) (FIFRA AI) (Ref. 3). Aquatic acute toxicity values for dodine include a daphnid 48-hour EC sub 50 of 17.8 ppb. EPA believes that there is sufficient evidence for listing dodine on EPCRA section 313 pursuant to EPCRA section 313(d)(2)(C) based on the available environmental toxicity data.
